All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, IContainerType, IGISObject, VisitableGeometry, IDataSerializable
public class ContainerStart extends Common implements IContainerType
We've seen the start of a container. A container can hold zero or more features and zero or more sub containers.

DRAND, J.Mathews

    • ContainerStart

      public ContainerStart(String type)
      Constructs a container that can hold zero or more features or other containers. ContainerStart should be followed by a matching ContainerEnd element.
      Parameters:
      type - Type of container
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if type is null or empty
